comment_data.body: Do you have a module SDK setup for your project?  What errors are you seeing?

Yes I have set the flutter/dart sdk on this project. Basically I set up a fresh everything as described on flutter.io and created a new standard project. "Flutter Demo Home Page". All I change is adding a plugin (any) and I get this error:
https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37406301/37550330-1a98dd0c-29d7-11e8-939d-a8bc1691e43c.png
(This is not my image, but I saw it in issue 1929)
I feel there is just a setting mistake that I have to change somewhere. The plugins are not being installed in the location it shows.

Thanks for following up @arieosdmin.

@stevemessick : does this repro for you?
@pq Nope, I had no problems when I was helping out with the code lab. Sorry, no time to investigate now.
Hello, I have the same problem. @arieosdmin have you fixed yours?

It is a real problem that I don't understand as I am very new with flutter and app development. There is another thread that they gave a solution, maybe it helps you it did not help me.
https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/issues/1929

The way I solved it is someone else who create a git for me and I imported that in Intelij IDEA. And I used that project to create my app. Then there is no problem with this plugin. Why? Don't have any idea.

@arieosdmin  thank you. I tried to follow the instructions on the thread but intellij idea shows an error when i try the flutter -> Open Android module in Android Studio. Says it's unable to locate android studio. I have android studio though so i dunno what the problem is. Maybe theres a way to tell itellij idea where android studio is located?

Thanks! Just to clarify:

- this is the working repo (the repo that was shared with you that doesn't have issues)
- it was shared ~like this? I note that it doesn't have any `.idea/` directory files committed (which they're normally not committed, but I would think that things like the `.idea/modules.xml` file would be useful in a full repro)

So I played around a little with the project @arieosdmin shared.
Turns out You have to: 
- delete the android.iml file if you have it, only iml files you should be left with are projectname.iml and projectname_android.iml
- Open project structure in intellij (ctrl-alt-shift-s)
- Delete the Flutter for Android library from libraries
- If your project has two modules in the module tab: one with the "projectname" and one with the "projectname_android", delete the module with the android suffix.
- Try rebuilding your project, any errors that come up now should be very straightforward to fix .
- That should fix the problem. 

It fixed mine. Thanks for all the help

There have been a lot of changes in the Android portion of a Flutter project. I can't reproduce any of the issues reported here with the current release. I'm closing this but feel free to re-open if the problem recurs.
